** Introduction to HTML forms:
   --------------------------

1) <input type="range">	-	slider
2) <input type="email">	-	e-mail address
3) <input type="date">	-	date-picker
4) <input type="url"> 	-	url-box (with a .com button, as in smartphones while opening web-browser)




** Other Introductions (related to HTML) :
   -------------------------------------

1) Geolocation :	ability to pin-point physical location in the browser.
2) Offline Storage :	ability to download and store required files in advance, which can be make use of in the event of lack of internet connection.
3) The Canvas Element :	a resolution dependent bitmap-canvas, used for rendering graphs, game graphics or other visual images on-the-fly.




