** Box Shadow :
   ----------

box shadow: 2px 2px 10px black;		-- offset x-axis, offset y-axis, amount of blur, color



** Defining FONT-NAME ALIAS :
   ------------------------

@font-face {
  font-family: mf;
  src:  url(/fonts/monkeyfeature.ttf/)
}

-> font-family: mf   can now be used anywhere in the stylesheet.


-> Font-squirrel or Google Web fonts provide free online fonts.

-> Using Font-squirrel new fonts can be created.

-> Typekit & FontDeck provides paid fonts.



**Using GOOGLE WEB FONTS :-
  ----------------------

-> Visit http://www.google.com/webfonts/

-> Select one of the fonts from the lists by clicking on it.

-> Select "Use This Font" Option

-> Copy the html code generated and paste it on your html page.





